The strongest univariate signals were led by feature_041, feature_055, and feature_027, all with statistically significant signed associations with pfs_months. The all-feature model retained several independent associations, led by feature_041, feature_025, and feature_036, indicating that some apparent main effects were not merely proxies for the other recorded features.
Subgroup heterogeneity was most evident for feature_036 with feature_065: the joint feature_036=1/feature_065=1 subgroup differed from additivity by -4.25 months (p=<1e-300). Stratified simple-effect checks confirmed that the effect of each member of the pair changed materially across levels of the other.
Among continuous-by-binary probes, feature_029 by feature_043 showed the strongest modification of slope (-0.0252 months per unit, p=<1e-300), supporting additional heterogeneity beyond purely binary subgroups.
